summary: I HAVE A 2002 JEEP LIBERTY.  THERE ARE TWO CYLINDERS UNDER THE HOOD THAT ARE SUPPOSED TO KEEP THE HOOD OPEN AFTER IT IS RAISED. MINE NO LONGER DO THAT. THIS COULD PRESENT A SERIOUS PROBLEM AS THE HOOD COULD SLAM DOWN UNTO ANYONE THAT MIGHT BE LOOKING UNDER THE HOOD. I LUCKILY AVOIDED GETTING INJURED THIS MORNING AS I WAS LOOKING UNDER THE HOOD, TURNED AROUND FOR A SECOND, AND THE HOOD SLAMMED SHUT, NARROWLY MISSING ME.    THERE IS A SIMILAR SITUATION WITH THE BACK WINDOW. ALTHOUGH NOT AS SERIOUS, THE CYLINDERS ON THE WINDOW ARE FAILING AS WELL. *TR
